Good news for residents, some of whom have not had running water for more than a week now, is that the Vhembe District Municipality (VDM) has resumed pumping water from the Albasini water plant. VDM just announced that the electrical equipment at the Albasini raw water plant have been fixed  and pumping have started at 04:15 this morning. “Water will be firstly pumped to Mowkop reservoir before supplying to residents … We thank Louis Trichardt town and Tshikota for their patience. We further apologise for the inconvenience caused,” said the VDM in a press release.